ique (main-d'oeuvre, immobilier, services).","questionnaireDesc":"Un outil de cadrage complet pour definir vos besoins logistiques aupres des partenaires shelter ou 3PL.","brochureDesc":"Telechargez notre guide complet de la fabrication en Basse-Californie avec Nearshore Navigator.","insightsTitle":"Veille marche","insightsDesc":"Dernieres tendances, donnees salariales et mises a jour reglementaires de la region frontaliere.","heroBadge":"Centre de ressources","heroTitle":"Outils pour votre","heroTitleHighlight":"Expansion","heroDesc":"Calculateurs, cartes et guides pour vous aider a naviguer dans le paysage industriel de la Basse-Californie en toute confiance.","ctaViewMap":"Voir la carte","ctaStartAssessment":"Demarrer l'evaluation","ctaLaunchTool":"Lancer l'outil","ctaDownload":"Voir et telecharger"},"brochure":{"title":"Nearshore Navigator","subtitle":"Your Strategic Partner for Manufacturing in Baja California","whyBaja":"Why Baja California?","proximity":"Proximity to USA","proximityDesc":"Just 20 minutes from San Diego, enabling executive oversight and JIT logistics.","labor":"Skilled Workforce","laborDesc":"Access to over 700,000 manufacturing workers with aerospace, medical device, and electronics experience.","infrastructure":"World-Class Infrastructure","infrastructureDesc":"Over 70 industrial parks with Class A buildings, high-speed fiber, and reliable utilities.","services":"Our Core Services","realEstate":"Industrial Real Estate","shelter":"Shelter Services","mfg":"Contract Manufacturing","contact":"Contact Us","download":"Download PDF","titlePreview":"Digital Brochure","subtitlePreview":"Preview of the downloadable PDF.","whyBajaSubtitle":"The premier destination for North American manufacturing.","realEstateDesc":"Site selection, BTS analysis, and lease negotiation for Class A industrial facilities.","shelterDesc":"Administrative and legal compliance services to launch operations in 90 days.","mfgDesc":"Partner matching with certified manufacturers for medical, aerospace, and electronics.","quote":"\"We help you align your operational needs with the reality of the Baja market to ensure a successful long-term investment.\"","leadershipTitle":"Leadership","denisseRole":"Director of Marketing & Business Development","hq":"San Diego HQ","ops":"Baja California Operations"},"assessment":{"liveData":"Live CFE Industrial Rates","costModelingDesc":"Detailed comparison of labor, real-time CFE electricity, and lease rates vs. your current operations."},"distributionPage":{"badge":"Logistique & Fulfillment","heroTitle":"Centres de distribution","heroTitleHighlight":"Baja California","heroSubtitle":"Optimisez votre chaîne d'approvisionnement avec des solutions de cross-border fulfillment et 3PL au port d'entrée terrestre le plus fréquenté de l'hémisphère occidental.","statsBorderCrossings":"Passages frontaliers","statsToLA":"À Los Angeles","statsCAConsumers":"Consommateurs CA","statsDuty":"Exonération (<$800)","whyTijuanaTitle":"Pourquoi choisir la Basse-Californie pour la distribution ?","sameDayTitle":"Livraison le jour même en CA","sameDayDesc":"Atteignez 40 millions de consommateurs en Californie du Sud en quelques heures.","section321Title":"Conformité Section 321","section321Desc":"Expédiez en franchise de droits aux consommateurs américains pour les commandes de moins de 800 $.","portsTitle":"2 ports d'entrée","portsDesc":"Passages d'Otay Mesa et de San Ysidro pour un routage flexible.","transloadingTitle":"Services de transbordement","transloadingDesc":"Changez de conteneur entre le rail, le camion et l'air en toute transparence.","strategicTitle":"Emplacement frontalier stratégique","strategicText1":"La Basse-Californie est adjacente à San Diego, offrant un accès immédiat au réseau autoroutier américain (I-5 et I-805).","strategicText2":"For e-commerce brands targeting the US West Coast market, Baja California acts as the perfect fulfillment hub — combining Mexican labor cost advantages with same-day delivery capabilities to Southern California.","availableServicesTitle":"Services disponibles","crossDocking":"Cross-docking & Transbordement","ecommerce":"Fulfillment E-commerce","inventoryManagement":"Systèmes de gestion des stocks","pickPackShip":"Préparation, emballage & expédition","returnsProcessing":"Traitement des retours","lastMile":"Partenaires de livraison du dernier kilomètre","customsBrokerage":"Courtage en douane","coldChain":"Logistique de la chaîne du froid","faqTitle":"Questions fréquemment posées","faq1Question":"What is Section 321 and how does it benefit e-commerce?","faq1Answer":"Section 321 is a US customs provision that allows duty-free import of goods valued under $800 per recipient per day. By shipping from a Baja California fulfillment center directly to US consumers, e-commerce brands can avoid import duties entirely on qualifying orders.","faq2Question":"How long does it take to cross the border?","faq2Answer":"FAST-lane enabled carriers with C-TPAT certification can cross in under 30 minutes during off-peak hours. Standard commercial crossings average 1-2 hours. We work with 3PL partners that have priority crossing privileges.","faq3Question":"Can you handle cold chain / temperature-controlled goods?","faq3Answer":"Yes. Several of our 3PL partners offer temperature-controlled warehousing and transportation for food, pharmaceuticals, and other perishable goods requiring cold chain integrity.","guideCTA":"View Our Section 321 Master Guide","guideDesc":"Save up to 25% on tariffs by fulfilling US orders from Tijuana.","questionnaireCTA":"Start 3PL Assessment","questionnaireDesc":"Complete our 36-point operational questionnaire to receive a customized logistics proposal.","formTitle":"Obtenez un devis logistique","formSubtitle":"Connectez-vous avec des partenaires 3PL et de distribution vérifiés en Basse-Californie."},"contractPage":{"badge":"Partenaires Maquiladora","heroTitle":"Fabrication en sous-traitance","heroTitleHighlight":"Baja California","heroSubtitle":"Vous ne voulez pas gérer une usine ? Associez-vous à des fabricants établis en Basse-Californie qui disposent déjà de l'équipement, des certifications et d'une main-d'œuvre formée.","whyContractTitle":"Pourquoi la fabrication en sous-traitance ?","establishedTitle":"Installations établies","establishedDesc":"Sautez les 2 ans de phase de démarrage. Associez-vous à des fabricants produisant déjà.","ipTitle":"Votre IP protégée","ipDesc":"Approche NDA en premier. Les fabricants s'occupent de la production, vous êtes propriétaire des designs.","certifiedTitle":"Pré-certifié","certifiedDesc":"Nous vous mettons en relation avec des CM détenant déjà vos certifications industrielles requises.","workforceTitle":"Main-d'œuvre formée","workforceDesc":"La Basse-Californie compte plus de 700 000 ouvriers de production avec des décennies d'expérience.","industriesTitle":"Secteurs d'activité","medicalDevices":"Medical Devices","medicalDesc":"Clean room assembly (ISO Class 7/8) for Class I, II, and III devices. ISO 13485 certified.","electronics":"Electronics","electronicsDesc":"PCB assembly, SMT lines, wire harness, and consumer electronics manufacturing.","aerospace":"Aerospace","aerospaceDesc":"Precision components, sub-assemblies, and MRO services for commercial and defense.","automotive":"Automotive","automotiveDesc":"Sub-assembly, upholstery, injection molding, and wire harness for OEMs and Tier 1/2 suppliers.","processTitle":"Our Process","step1Title":"Define Requirements","step1Desc":"Share your product specs, volume needs, quality standards, and certification requirements.","step2Title":"Receive Shortlist","step2Desc":"We curate 3-5 contract manufacturers that match your criteria, all pre-vetted.","step3Title":"Visit & Evaluate","step3Desc":"Tour facilities, meet management, assess capabilities, and review quality systems.","step4Title":"Negotiate & Launch","step4Desc":"We assist with contract terms, pricing negotiation, and production ramp-up.","faqTitle":"Frequently Asked Questions","faq1Question":"What minimum order volumes do CMs require?","faq1Answer":"This varies by industry and complexity. Medical device CMs often start at $500K-$1M annual spend. Electronics CMs may accept lower volumes for high-mix products. We match you with partners suited to your scale.","faq2Question":"How is intellectual property protected?","faq2Answer":"All relationships begin with NDAs. Mexican IP law is USMCA-aligned, providing strong protections. We recommend registering patents/trademarks in Mexico as well. CMs typically sign non-compete clauses for your product category.","faq3Question":"Can I audit the factory before committing?","faq3Answer":"Absolutely. We encourage and facilitate site visits. Most clients conduct 1-2 day audits covering quality systems, production capabilities, workforce, and financial stability before making a decision.","faq4Question":"What certifications should I look for?","faq4Answer":"Medical: ISO 13485, FDA Registration. Automotive: IATF 16949. Aerospace: AS9100D, NADCAP. Electronics: IPC-A-610, ISO 9001. We only match you with CMs holding your required certifications.","formTitle":"Request a Vendor Shortlist","formSubtitle":"Tell us your product, volume, and certification requirements. We'll curate 3-5 pre-vetted contract manufacturers.","strategyTitle":"Matchmaking & Due Diligence","strategySubtitle":"We move beyond simple introductions. We meticulously vet suppliers and protect your IP to de-risk your entry into Mexico.","capabilityTitle":"Supplier Capability Surveys","capabilityDesc":"Deep-dive surveys into engineering, quality systems, and financial health—not just a name and a website.","roadmapTitle":"Expansion Roadmaps","roadmapDesc":"Plan your 'de-risking' strategy: Start with a contract partner, then transition to your own facility as you scale.","safeguardsTitle":"IP & Quality Safeguards","safeguardsDesc":"We act as your local eyes and ears, managing pricing, pilot runs, and routine audits to ensure US standards.","furniture":"Mobilier","furnitureDesc":"Fabrication contractuelle axee sur la qualite pour les constructions commerciales avec coherence des finitions et preparation a l'emballage.","cnc":"Usinage CNC de precision","cncDesc":"Usinage de precision certifie AS9100 pour les applications aerospatiales et commerciales a tolerances serrees.","regionsSubtitle":"Regions principales: Basse-Californie et Monterrey / Nuevo Leon, avec une couverture plus large selon les procedes et certifications.","faq5Question":"Do you own the factories?","faq5Answer":"We work with a vetted network of Contract Manufacturers (CMs). We do not own the factories, but handle the due diligence and quality oversight.","faq6Question":"What is the minimum order quantity (MOQ)?","faq6Answer":"MOQs vary by manufacturer and product. It is generally best for companies looking to scale beyond prototyping.","faq7Question":"How do you handle Quality Control (QC)?","faq7Answer":"QC is handled via the CM's internal ISO certifications and our own external audits.","faq8Question":"Can I bring my own raw materials?","faq8Answer":"Yes, this is called \"consignment.\" Materials can be shipped tax-free via the IMMEX program.","faq9Question":"Does contract manufacturing protect my IP?","faq9Answer":"Yes, we ensure strict NDAs and multi-layered IP protection frameworks aligned with US standards.","faq10Question":"Who manages the logistics?","faq11Answer":"Typically set as Ex-Works. We connect you with logistics partners to handle the cross-border import process."},"realEstatePage":{"heroTitle":"Industrial Real Estate in","heroTitleHighlight":"Baja California","heroSubtitle":"Secure the perfect industrial space for your manufacturing or logistics operation in Mexico's top border city.","premiumTitle":"Premium Industrial Spaces","premiumText1":"Baja California offers over 70 million square feet of industrial inventory. Whether you need a 20,000 sq. ft. light assembly facility or a 200,000 sq. ft. distribution center, we help you navigate the market to find the right property.","premiumText2":"We have relationships with all major industrial developers in the region, including Vesta, Prologis, and local groups, ensuring you get access to both on-market and off-market opportunities.","specsTitle":"Typical Building Specs","clearHeight":"Clear Height","dockDoors":"Dock Doors","floorLoad":"Floor Load","power":"Power","whyTijuanaTitle":"Why Baja California?","classA":"Class A Industrial Buildings","builtToSuit":"Built-to-Suit Projects","landForDev":"Land for Development","flexibleLease":"Flexible Lease Terms","crossDocking":"Cross-Docking Facilities","otayProximity":"Otay Mesa Proximity","faqTitle":"Frequently Asked Questions","faq1Question":"What are the current lease rates?","faq1Answer":"Lease rates in Baja California typically range from $0.75 to $0.95 USD per sq. ft. per month (NNN), depending on location and building class.","faq2Question":"What is the typical lease term?","faq2Answer":"Standard industrial lease terms are usually 3 to 5 years, though longer terms (7-10 years) may be required for built-to-suit projects.","formTitle":"Find Available Space","formSubtitle":"Tell us your requirements and we'll send you a curated list of available properties.","strategyTitle":"Strategy-Led Site Selection","strategySubtitle":"More than just finding a building. We perform technical audits and comparative studies to ensure your site supports your long-term operation.","utilityTitle":"Utility & Infrastructure Audits","utilityDesc":"We verify substation capacity and water availability before you sign, mitigating the risk of utility shortages.","comparativeTitle":"Multi-City Comparative Studies","comparativeDesc":"TCO analysis comparing Baja California vs. Bajío or other regions to quantify your total landed cost.","tenantTitle":"Tenant Mindset Analysis","tenantDesc":"Expert advice on Build-to-Suit vs. Existing Inventory to maximize leverage in a low-vacancy market.","faq3Question":"What are the average lease rates for Class A industrial space in Baja?","faq3Answer":"Lease rates for Class A industrial space in Baja California typically range from /bin/zsh.75 to /bin/zsh.85 USD per square foot per month, depending on location and amenities.","faq4Question":"Can foreigners buy industrial land in Baja California?","faq4Answer":"Yes, foreigners can acquire land in Mexico's restricted zone through a \"Fideicomiso\" (Bank Trust), granting full ownership rights.","faq5Question":"How long does a Build-to-Suit project take?","faq5Answer":"A typical Build-to-Suit (BTS) project in Baja California takes between 8 to 12 months from groundbreaking to occupancy.","faq6Question":"What is the difference between Shell and Turnkey leases?","faq6Answer":"A \"Shell\" lease provides the basic structure, while a \"Turnkey\" lease includes all specified improvements, ready for operation.","faq7Question":"Are Triple Net (NNN) leases common in Mexico?","faq7Answer":"Yes, most industrial leases are NNN, meaning the tenant pays for property taxes, insurance, and maintenance.","faq8Question":"What utilities are available in Baja industrial parks?","faq8Answer":"Major parks offer high-voltage power, natural gas, fiber-optic internet, and treated water/sewage systems.","faq9Question":"How close are these parks to the US border?","faq9Answer":"Most Class A parks in Tijuana and Mexicali are located within 20-30 minutes of commercial border crossings.","linkB2C":"Exploring B2C? View our Section 321 Distribution Guide","badgeParks":"70+ Class A Industrial Parks"},"callCenterPage":{"badge":"BPO & Call Center Services","heroTitle":"Call Center Solutions in","heroTitleHighlight":"Baja California","heroSubtitle":"Scale your customer support operations with Baja California's world-class bilingual workforce at a fraction of US costs.","whyTijuanaTitle":"Why Baja California for BPO?","costSavingsTitle":"40-60% Cost Savings","costSavingsDesc":"Reduce operational costs compared to US-based call centers while maintaining quality.","agentsTitle":"50,000+ Bilingual Agents","agentsDesc":"Access a deep talent pool of English and Spanish speaking professionals.","timezoneTitle":"Pacific Time Zone","timezoneDesc":"Same working hours as California for real-time collaboration and oversight.","cultureTitle":"Cultural Alignment","cultureDesc":"Agents familiar with US culture and customer expectations.","servicesTitle":"Services We Connect You With","inboundSupport":"Inbound Customer Support","outboundSales":"Outbound Sales & Lead Generation","techSupport":"Technical Support (Tier 1 & 2)","backOffice":"Back Office Processing","chatEmail":"Chat & Email Support","bilingual":"Bilingual (EN/ES) Services","glanceTitle":"Baja California BPO at a Glance","bilingualAgents":"Bilingual Agents","costSavings":"Cost Savings","timeZone":"Time Zone","agentRetention":"Agent Retention","formTitle":"Get a BPO Consultation","formSubtitle":"Tell us about your support needs and we'll connect you with vetted call center partners."},"s321":{"regulatoryAlert":"2026 Regulatory Update","heroTitle":"Section 321","heroTitleHighlight":"Master Guide","heroSubtitle":"Navigate the 2025 de minimis suspension and discover compliant Section 321 distribution strategies in Mexico.","whatIsTitle":"Section 321 Distribution in 2026","whatIsDesc":"Section 321 has historically been a massive advantage for e-commerce. However, recent US Customs suspensions have changed the rules. Understanding the pivot to IMMEX and Bonded strategies is now mandatory for cost-effective fulfillment.","suspensionTitle":"August 2025 Suspension Notice","suspensionDesc":"CBP has fully suspended Section 321 de minimis for commercial shipments. All B2C entries now require full customs processing, making 'Alternative Routing' the new standard.","pivotTitle":"IMMEX Pivot","pivotDesc":"Utilize Mexico's IMMEX program to defer duties and manage consolidated container entries effectively.","complianceTitle":"Risk Mitigation","complianceDesc":"Ensure your supply chain remains compliant with the new Type 86 restrictions and USMCA 2026 protocols.","whyBajaTitle":"Why Baja California?","whyBaja1":"20 Minutes from San Diego border crossings","whyBaja2":"Access to low-cost, high-quality Mexican logistics labor","whyBaja3":"Same-day injection into the US domestic shipping system","whyBaja4":"Significant savings on returns processing and reverse logistics","processTitle":"The 2026 Process","step1Title":"Cargo Arrival","step1Desc":"Your goods arrive at the Port of Ensenada or Port of Long Beach in 'Bonded' status.","step2Title":"Bonded Storage","step2Desc":"Kitting, labeling, and storage in a world-class Tijuana facility without paying duties.","step3Title":"Consolidated Manifest","step3Desc":"B2C orders are prepared as consolidated entries under new regulatory protocols.","step4Title":"Border Clearance","step4Desc":"Processed via specialized lanes and handed over to US carriers in San Diego.","formTitle":"Section 321 Consultation","formSubtitle":"Schedule a call to discuss your 2026 de minimis strategy and alternative routing."},"broker":{"advisorTitle":"Objective Advisor","advisorDesc":"We don't own the buildings; we navigate the market to find you the perfect fit.","matchmakingTitle":"Expert Matchmaking","matchmakingDesc":"Connecting you with vetted CMs and shelter providers based on performance data.","networkTitle":"Vetted Network","networkDesc":"Direct access to 70+ industrial parks and top-tier logistics operators."},"questionnaire":{"title":"3PL Operation Questionnaire","subtitle":"Confidential Assessment","intro":"Please provide the following information to help us understand your operation requirements.","sec1_title":"1. Operational Basics","q1":"How many square feet do you need for your operation?","q2":"What kind of products would you be moving with us?","q3":"What is the presentation of the product we will be receiving? (standard pallets, bulk, bags, packages, etc.)","q4":"Please provide the dimensions in inches of the packages or pallets we will be receiving (length, width, height).","q5":"What is the average weight in pounds of the pallets?","sec2_title":"2. Inventory & Handling","q6":"What are the tariff fractions of the products we would be storing?","q7":"Are any of the products Hazmat?","q8":"How many levels can the pallets be stacked one on top of the other?","q9":"How many orders are we going to process per day?","q10":"How many pieces does a typical order consist of?","q11":"Are we going to do virtual transfers or are we going to do home extension?","q12":"Explain the process you need to be carried out within the Distribution Center. (Attach diagram/doc if needed)","sec3_title":"3. Systems & Communication","q13":"How will you transmit the orders to us?","q14":"What is the order management system you use?","q15":"How often would you be transmitting the orders to us?","q16":"What would be the order transmission protocol? (AS2, FTP, SFTP, Mail, OTHER)","q17":"What will be the content of the transmission? (EDI ANSI X12, PLAIN TEXT CSV/TAB/PIPE)","q18":"Please provide an example of the commands you would transmit to us for testing.","sec4_title":"4. Volume & Capacity","q19":"Do you have an estimate of the number of personnel required?","q20":"Do you have an estimate of the number of pallets positions to store?","q21":"How many trailer loads will we receive per week?","q22":"How many pallets will fit in each trailer load?","q23":"How many orders or units will we be shipping per day?","sec5_title":"5. Logistics & Additional Info","q24":"Are there any current operations we can visit?","q25":"How many part numbers go on an average order?","q26":"How many SKU's do you handle in total? (Attach catalog if possible)","q27":"How many units/cartons fit on a standard 40\"x48\"x60\" pallet?","q28":"Do you need special equipment? (sewing machines, cutting machines, etc.)","q29":"What are the destinations we would be shipping to?","q30":"What is the company that owns the merchandise?","q31":"Which company would we bill for our services?","sec6_title":"6. Value, Insurance & Transport","q32":"What would be the total value of the merchandise to be held?","q33":"Do you agree to extend your policy to insure the merchandise?","q34":"What is the period for which you require our services?","q35":"Can we offer you quotes for transportation? What are the addresses?","q36":"What Annex 24 system do you use?","printPdf":"Click here to Print / Save as PDF"},"cost_calculator":{"metaTitle":"Calculateur de Coûts de Fabrication en Basse-Californie | Nearshore Navigator","metaDesc":"Estimez vos coûts de fabrication entièrement intégrés en Basse-Californie par rapport aux coûts nationaux américains. Outil interactif gratuit.","title":"Calculateur de Coûts de Fabrication en Basse-Californie","subtitle":"Estimez vos coûts de fabrication entièrement intégrés au Mexique par rapport aux coûts nationaux américains."},"park_map":{"metaTitle":"Carte des Parcs Industriels de Basse-Californie (2026) | Nearshore Navigator","metaDesc":"Guide complet des parcs industriels de Basse-Californie. Comparez la disponibilité de classe A, les taux de location et les emplacements à Tijuana, Mexicali et Tecate.","title":"Carte des Parcs Industriels de Basse-Californie (2026)","subtitle":"Explorez l'espace de fabrication de classe A et B à travers Tijuana, Mexicali et Tecate. Les données reflètent les taux de location NNN actuels et les statuts de vacance du marché.","tableTitle":"Disponibilité du Marché et Taux de Location","ctaTitle":"Besoin d'aide pour sécuriser de l'espace dans ces parcs?","ctaDesc":"Les taux de vacance dans les installations de classe A sont inférieurs à 3%. Parlez directement avec Denisse Martinez pour contourner les listes d'attente et modéliser votre empreinte nearshore."},"home":{"metaTitle":"Fabrication Nearshore en Basse-Californie | Economies 40-60% | Nearshore Navigator","metaDescription":"Conseil strategique pour les entreprises americaines qui developpent leur production a Tijuana et en Basse-Californie. Reduisez les couts de 40 a 60%, acces a 50K+ travailleurs bilingues, operationnel en 90 jours a 20 minutes de San Diego.","heroImageAlt":"Vue aerienne du parc industriel de Tijuana"},"aboutPage":{"mainHeading":"Transformer 'nous voulons le Mexique' en une prochaine etape claire","mainSub":"Nearshore Navigator existe pour faciliter les decisions: des conseils fondes, un suivi rigoureux et un soutien a l'execution adapte a votre realite.","struggleTitle":"Le defi commun","struggleDesc":"Les decisions de nearshoring se bloquent souvent apres l'enthousiasme initial -- quand les vraies questions surgissent:","struggleList1":"Ou en Basse-Californie devrions-nous nous installer?","struggleList2":"A quoi ressemblera la structure des couts?","struggleList3":"Location, Shelter ou Contrat?","approachTitle":"Notre approche","approachDesc":"Nous ne sommes ni un annuaire ni une solution universelle. Chaque projet a des contraintes differentes.","approachList1":"Analyse du calendrier et de l'empreinte","approachList2":"Besoins en main-d'oeuvre et certifications","approachList3":"Logistique et tolerance au risque","tier2Badge":"Pour les fabricants en croissance","tier2Title":"La realite des fournisseurs de rang 2","tier2Desc":"Etes-vous un fournisseur de taille moyenne sous pression? Assez grand pour avoir besoin du Mexique, mais trop lean pour mobiliser une equipe de lancement de 20 personnes?","trapTitle":"Le piege","trapDesc":"Essayer de copier une expansion GM/Ford sans leur budget cree un chaos administratif.","fixTitle":"La solution","fixDesc":"Nous structurons des accords Shelter qui vous permettent de posseder l'equipement et les processus, tandis qu'un tiers gere les contraintes RH et douanieres.","leadershipBadge":"Direction","denisseName":"Denisse Martinez","denisseTitle":"Directrice Marketing et Conseillere","denisseBio1":"Avec plus d'une decennie d'experience dans le developpement economique et la croissance industrielle dans la region Cali-Baja, Denisse apporte une approche strategique et basee sur les donnees au nearshoring.","denisseBio2":"Ayant soutenu le lancement et la croissance d'operations de fabrication dans le corridor Cali-Baja, elle comprend que le succes d'une expansion ne se resume pas a trouver un batiment -- il s'agit de batir une operation durable.","denisseBio3":"Chez Nearshore Navigator, Denisse adopte une philosophie 'client en premier', en veillant a ce que chaque recommandation soit fondee sur des donnees terrain.","connect":"Se connecter avec Denisse","toolkitTitle":"Une boite a outils pratique pour l'expansion","toolkitDesc":"Les entreprises n'entrent pas toutes au Mexique de la meme maniere. Nous vous aidons a evaluer la meilleure voie.","cardRealEstateTitle":"Immobilier industriel et selection de site","cardRealEstateDesc":"Preseletion d'options de sites adaptees a vos besoins, organisation de visites productives, elaboration de comparatifs decisionnels et accompagnement dans les negociations.","cardContractTitle":"Mise en relation avec des partenaires de fabrication contractuelle","cardContractDesc":"Nous vous aidons a demarrer correctement: definir les exigences, entrer en contact avec des fournisseurs qualifies et piloter l'evaluation.","cardShelterServicesTitle":"Atterrissage strategique en douceur","cardShelterServicesDesc":"Quand la rapidite compte. Nous vous aidons a evaluer la voie d'entree la plus efficace et a presenter des options verifiees.","cardCtaLearnMore":"En savoir plus","cardCtaRequest":"Demander une evaluation","processTitle":"Un processus sans detours qui maintient les projets en mouvement","step1Title":"Decouverte","step1Desc":"Objectifs, empreinte, exigences, calendrier","step2Title":"Evaluation","step2Desc":"La voie la plus pratique pour votre situation","step3Title":"Preseletion et plan","step3Desc":"Des options claires avec les compromis expliques","step4Title":"Visites et diligence raisonnable","step4Desc":"Agendas structures, comparatifs, aide a la decision","step5Title":"Prochaines etapes","step5Desc":"Introductions et accompagnement vers l'execution","controlText":"Vous gardez le controle. Nous apportons structure, realisme et elan.","bajaTitle":"Nous couvrons toute la Basse-Californie","bajaDesc":"Nous accompagnons les projets dans toute la Basse-Californie. Notre mission est de vous aider a aligner ces variables et a prendre une decision eclairee plus rapidement.","mapBtn":"Traceons ensemble votre meilleur chemin","finalTitle":"Traceons ensemble votre meilleur chemin en Basse-Californie","finalDesc":"Dites-nous ce que vous construisez et quand vous devez etre operationnel. Nous vous aiderons a identifier le point de depart le plus judicieux.","scheduleBtn":"Planifier un appel de decouverte","assessmentBtn":"Demander une evaluation de localisation"},"caseStudies":{"badge":"Resultats terrain","title":"Projets d'expansion que nous avons soutenus","subtitle":"Des resultats concrets pour les fabricants qui ont avance avec structure et les bons partenaires.","case1_tag":"Aerospatiale / Basse-Californie","case1_title":"Fournisseur de faisceaux de rang 1 entre au Mexique en 90 jours","case1_challenge":"Un fabricant californien de faisceaux de cables aerospatiaux devait reduire ses couts sans perturber ses delais de livraison ni ses exigences AS9100.","case1_solution":"Nous avons structure un accord Shelter a Mexicali et gere l'ensemble du calendrier de transition de l'evaluation a la production.","case1_result1":"42% de reduction des couts de main-d'oeuvre directe vs reference californienne","case1_result2":"Operations lancees dans les 90 jours suivant l'evaluation initiale","case1_result3":"Aucune lacune de certification -- AS9100 maintenue tout au long","case2_tag":"Dispositifs medicaux / Tijuana","case2_title":"Une startup trouve un partenaire ISO 13485 sans tracas de visite de site","case2_challenge":"Une startup de dispositifs medicaux avait besoin d'un fabricant contractuel pour l'assemblage de dispositifs de classe II mais manquait des ressources internes pour evaluer des installations au Mexique.","case2_solution":"Nous avons defini leurs exigences, preselectonne 12 partenaires potentiels reduits a 4, et soutenu les negociations de NDA et de contrat.","case2_result1":"Fabricant certifie ISO 13485 selectionne avec enregistrement FDA deja en place","case2_result2":"Production pilote lancee dans les 6 mois suivant le premier appel","case2_result3":"Cadre complet de protection IP etabli avant le debut de la production","case3_tag":"Fabrication contractuelle / Mobilier","case3_title":"Une marque DTC de mobilier economise 1,2M$ vs le reshoring asiatique","case3_challenge":"Une marque de mobilier DTC envisageait de relocaliser depuis le Vietnam en raison de l'exposition aux droits de douane et des longs delais.","case3_solution":"Nous avons presente une option en Basse-Californie avec une analyse du cout total debarque, coordonne deux visites d'installations et mene la negociation commerciale.","case3_result1":"1,2M$ d'economies projetees sur 3 ans vs production domestique americaine","case3_result2":"Delais reduits de 14 semaines (Asie) a 5 jours (Tijuana vers Los Angeles)","case3_result3":"Aucune exposition aux droits de douane -- ACEUM qualifie des le premier jour"},"bio_denisse":{"title":"Rencontrez Denisse Martinez | Consultante Nearshore en Basse-Californie","intro":"Une approche strategique de la fabrication au Mexique","backgroundTitle":"Parcours professionnel et leadership local","backgroundDesc":"Avec plus de 15 ans d'experience dans le corridor Cali-Baja, Denisse Martinez s'est imposee comme une reference dans le nearshoring nord-americain.","trackRecordTitle":"Plus de 20 entreprises accompagnees dans plusieurs secteurs","expertiseTitle":"Accreditations sectorielles et methodologie de selection de sites","expertiseDesc":"Denisse defend un modele de courtage objectif, garantissant que les fabricants americains re